Description: Rectangular bone object, probably a gaming board. Well-smoothed and shaped, the upper surface shows ridges from bone structure, while the rear is very smooth. An incised line at the front shows a rectangular following the outlines of the object. Parts of the surface broken off at one corner, whole object broken into 2 pieces, glued together.
Bibliographic references: Spencer 1997 / Amara West I, The Architectural Report (p. 155)
